He stepped upon the pad, and he was transported to the Combine spires, on Faydwer. He walked a path, looking at the forest, it was full of life... he sniffed the air, he felt the rangers tracking him. He kneeled down, he hoped they would not disturb his meditation, the only way he could keep the ache under control. <br>
Hours went by, Drachma breathed a sigh, his ache was subsiding, then he felt it, as the arrow penetrated his shoulder, the bone breaking... he laid down, nursing his shoulder, and began to growl.... the first time in his life, he lost all feeling, he had no thought... he turned into an animal... he sttod up, and charged the young ranger, and tore him apart, his freinds came to help, but a similiar fate came to the young boys, barely in their teens... he picked up the elf, and began to feed, he roared, the ache began to subside, and with it, his mind came back, and he looked down at the mutilated boy, he looked sown at his hands covered in blood.... he grabbed his pack and fled the forest....<br>
Thoughts of Seraphimm, came into his mind.... the curse of stupidity was nothing compared to the ache.... the curse of Love...of Ogur love.... for Ogurs are the most feeling of any race.... once they fall in love.... they can never go back to their lives.... but none had ever suffered the ache.... those who have, die.... why didn't he.... She had cursed him.... he had to avoid her... for the ache grows stronger, when she is near....<br>
&quot; maybe one day I will be free of the ache.... but until then, I must wander.... oh Trachma I how we are bound....&quot;<br>
<br>
Drachma walked into the mountains of Butcher Block where his father was murdered.... this was a journey of rememberance...what he would find on this journey only Zek knows...  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.silentredemption.org/images/112102/ogre.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
